cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the development of a deep convolutional neural network architecture for disambiguation of road junctions for autonomous vehicles. This involves computer vision techniques and robotics, which are covered under the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning algorithms and neural networks for classification falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses potential security risks associated with autonomous vehicles, which falls under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
